channel.title: Great learning opportunity....(377)
channel.description:
Ok, do not give me any credits. i only spent a measly 5 minutes slapping together some fixes. note, this isn't my 377 with walking lol... I wont release my walking one. But this is a great learning opportunity for some people. people that want to rise above the crowd. 95% Creds to winterlove. 5% to jagex for giving me my education in java and C/C++. [b] RapidShare [/b] Download Link 1: http://rapidshare.com/files/32304322/377_server.rar.html([b]Server[/b])
Download Link 2: http://rapidshare.com/files/32304799/377_Client.rar.html([b]Client[/b]) [b] Uppit [/b] Download Link 1: http://uppit.com/d/DQ0VC([b]Client[/b])
Download Link 2: http://uppit.com/d/DDBFR([b]Server[/b])
Like i said. please do not give me any credits. All i did was change the packets around so it would log-in, not very hard. but most people wouldn't have done that.
Btw, First person to get this completly working will litterally get a cookie lmao.

item.dc:creator: @aaa803 aaa803
item.description:
@aaa803 wrote:

[quote=“bakatool, post:42, topic:97488”]nice fix rofl

you said this.

try {
					fillInStream(2);
					if(inStream.readUnsignedByte() != 14) {
						shutdownError("Expected login Id 14 from client.");
						disconnected = true;
						return;
			}

replace that block with this

Code:

try {
					fillInStream(2);
					if(inStream.readUnsignedByte() != 14) {
						shutdownError("Expected login Id 14 from client.");
						disconnected = false;
						return;
			}

wouldn’t it be a better fix if sniffed the correct byte for this login? or just commented out it all not just change disconnected = false; as you know it still returns means it still exits thats pretty stupid lol.

since I don’t care about rs2 that much never worked with it either. Here would be my way of fixing this

try {
					fillInStream(2);
                                                                inStream.readUnsignedByte()

unless the packet structure changed this should work it pushes the byte in stream without doing anything else, you could of also commented out everything inside the if() brackets { /* */ }[/quote]

the new engine pings the server using 0 or 14
0 gives unexpected
so 14 is the correct login packet noob =p
